Static | The browsers default position and each element will take up space on its own line

Relative | Allows you to position an element relative to its static position. using (top, bottom, left, right)

Absolute | All other element will ignore the element and act like it is not present on the page. The element will be position relative to is closed positioned parent.

Fixed | The element will be fixed to its specific position, regardless of user scrolling. The element is also removed from the flow of the DOM.